# YAML Schema Conventions

The file `schema/moonraker_api.yaml` defines all Moonraker API endpoints.

## Structure

```yaml
namespaces:
  <namespace_name>:
    description: Human-readable description
    methods:
      <method_key>:
        rpc_method: JSON-RPC method name (e.g. printer.info)
        http_method: GET | POST | DELETE
        http_path: /url/path (or null for WS-only)
        description: What this method does
        transport: ws | http | both  (default: both)
        params:
          <param_name>:
            type: str | int | float | bool | list | dict | Any
            required: true | false
            description: What the parameter does
        returns:
          type: Python type annotation
          description: What is returned
```

## After Editing

Always regenerate bindings: `python scripts/generate_bindings.py`
Then commit both the YAML and the regenerated `_generated.py`.
